{
	"components": [
		{
			"id": "webhook_1",
			"provider": "webhook",
			"config": {}
		},
		{
			"id": "question_1",
			"provider": "question",
			"config": {},
			"input": [{ "lane": "text", "from": "webhook_1" }]
		},
		{
			"id": "agent_rocketride_1",
			"provider": "agent_rocketride",
			"config": {
				"instructions": [
					"You are the PaperDiff Compare pipeline. The incoming question contains a JSON body matching contracts/compare.md's request shape (left/right, each with url or claim). Respond with ONLY a single JSON object matching contracts/compare.md's response shape exactly: left, right, dimensions (array), verdict {headline, explanation}, synthesis, evidence_summary, trace (array). Return raw JSON only, no prose, no markdown fences.",
					"For each side (left/right) that has a url or DOI: call the linkup tool with method POST, url https://api.linkup.so/v1/fetch, bearer_token ${ROCKETRIDE_LINKUP_KEY}, body_json {\"url\": \"<the side's url, resolving a DOI to its landing page first if needed>\", \"outputFormat\": \"markdown\", \"renderJS\": true}. The response has a 'markdown' field with the page's cleaned content -- use it to fill that side's title, authors, venue, year, source_url, and to extract 2-4 short exact passages as evidence for the comparison dimensions. If the markdown looks like a bot-check/redirect page rather than real article content (e.g. mentions 'checking your browser', 'captcha', or is under ~200 characters), treat that side as fetch-failed rather than using it as real content. Record this retrieval as a trace entry with stage 'linkup_fetch' and its real status. If a side has no url, only a claim, skip Linkup for that side and use the provided claim text directly.",
					"For each dimension you compare, once you have a claim/passage pair for both sides, call the classifier tool with method POST, url https://cole-rim-festivals-deck.trycloudflare.com/score_batch, body_json {\"pairs\": [{\"claim\": \"<left side's stated position on this dimension>\", \"evidence\": \"<right side's exact passage or claim text>\"}]}. Use the returned label (supports/contradicts/insufficient) and product_state to set that dimension's classification and evidence_status -- do not invent these yourself. equivalent/different/incompatible in 'classification' should reflect whether the two sides materially agree, differ, or conflict on this dimension; evidence_status should be the classifier's product_state mapped to Grounded/Qualified/Needs review/flag as appropriate. Record each call as a trace entry with stage 'verifier_score'.",
					"Never fabricate a real DOI, a real evidence passage, or a peer-reviewed-evidence status. If a Linkup fetch or classifier call fails or returns nothing usable, record that failure honestly in trace and mark the affected dimension's evidence_status as 'Needs review' rather than inventing content."
				],
				"max_waves": 12,
				"parameters": {}
			},
			"input": [{ "lane": "questions", "from": "question_1" }]
		},
		{
			"id": "llm_openai_1",
			"provider": "llm_openai",
			"config": {
				"profile": "openai-4o",
				"openai-4o": { "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_OPENAI_KEY}" },
				"parameters": {}
			},
			"control": [
				{ "classType": "llm", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "memory_internal_1",
			"provider": "memory_internal",
			"config": { "type": "memory_internal" },
			"control": [
				{ "classType": "memory", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "tool_http_linkup",
			"provider": "tool_http_request",
			"config": {
				"serverName": "linkup",
				"allowGET": false,
				"allowPOST": true,
				"allowPUT": false,
				"allowPATCH": false,
				"allowDELETE": false,
				"urlWhitelist": ["^https://api\\.linkup\\.so/.*"]
			},
			"control": [
				{ "classType": "tool", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "tool_http_classifier",
			"provider": "tool_http_request",
			"config": {
				"serverName": "classifier",
				"allowGET": true,
				"allowPOST": true,
				"allowPUT": false,
				"allowPATCH": false,
				"allowDELETE": false,
				"urlWhitelist": ["^https://cole-rim-festivals-deck\\.trycloudflare\\.com/.*"]
			},
			"control": [
				{ "classType": "tool", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "response_answers_1",
			"provider": "response_answers",
			"config": { "laneName": "answers" },
			"input": [{ "lane": "answers", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }]
		}
	],
	"name": "paperdiff-compare",
	"description": "PaperDiff Compare pipeline -- webhook source, Linkup fetch + classifier tools wired to the agent.",
	"project_id": "9c3f6c2e-3f2b-4b7a-9a2e-1a7b7f6d2c41",
	"source": "webhook_1",
	"version": 1
}
